snippet.title: Young Jonn  - Cash Flow (feat. Wizkid) [Official Music Video]
snippet.description:
After back-to-back hits, Young Jonn returns with “Cash Flow” featuring Wizkid — a smooth anthem about living life soft, enjoying the fruits of success, and spending with ease. Opening with the reflective line “had a hard life but I live soft,” the track captures the transition from struggle to abundance, wrapped in Young Jonn’s jiggy energy and Wizkid’s signature calm delivery.

“Cash Flow” is more than a flex — it’s a celebration of growth, freedom, and the soft life. The record leads directly into Young Jonn’s highly anticipated project, Blue Disco, marking a new chapter in his sound and story.

🔵 Stream “Cash Flow” everywhere - https://youngjonn.lnk.to/cashflow

Follow Young Jonn
Twitter - https://bit.ly/3vK9iGV
Instagram - https://bit.ly/3IeRruq
Snapchat https://bit.ly/3JgXy2x
Tik Tok - https://www.tiktok.com/@youngjonn1

Listen here: 
Sooner:  https://YoungJonn.lnk.to/sooner
Jiggy Forever : https://YoungJonn.lnk.to/jiggyforever
Love Is Not Enough: https://youngjonn.lnk.to/LINEcc

About Young Jonn
John Saviours Udomboso, fondly known as Young Jonn "The Wicked Producer" is an award winning Afro-pop producer, singer/songwriter. Dubbed the Sound of the Streets, "Young Jonn" is the head huncho and musical genius behind some of the most memorable Artists that own the streets in the Street-Hop or Pop genre. With over 3 awards in some of the prestigious Awards in Nigeria, Young Jonn's sound, lyrics and beats have broken several legendary Artists on the Nigerian music scene since the mid-2000s.  Young Jonn's credits have established him as one of the most iconic producers in the last 10 years. Young Jonn signed an Artist Recording Agreement with Nigeria's foremost record label, Chocolate City with the aim to transition from being a producer to a Recording Artist. His first project Love Is Not Enough was released in the April 2022. In 2024, he released his long-awaited debut album, Jiggy Forever. The album boasts of anthems like Big Big Things, Aquafina, Sharpally, and Stronger.

Subscribe to Young Jonn's channel for all the best and latest official music videos, albums, behind the scenes, live performances and more!

snippet.title: Man Vs Baby | Official Trailer | Netflix
snippet.description:
After a job looking after a high-tech mansion ended in disaster thanks to an irritating insect in Man vs Bee, Trevor Bingley (Rowan Atkinson) has left the stressful world of housesitting for the quieter life of a school caretaker. That is, until a lucrative offer to look after a luxury London penthouse over Christmas proves too tempting to resist. But on the last day of term, when no one comes to collect the Baby Jesus from the school nativity, Trevor finds himself with another undersized and very unexpected companion. With a penthouse to protect and a baby to burp, will Trevor be able to have the calm Christmas he hopes for, or will festivities descend into chaos?

snippet.title: [Official Trailer] Burnout Syndrome ภาวะรักคนหมดไฟ
snippet.description:
Korean ก่อ กรวิก (ออฟ จุมพล) นักธุรกิจสตาร์ตอัปผู้เกลียดการเจอผู้คน จนกระทั่งวันหนึ่งเขาได้พบกับ จิระ (กัน อรรถพันธ์) ศิลปินหนุ่มตกงานที่กำลังค้นหาตัวตน ด้วยแรงดึงดูดอันแปลกประหลาดทำให้ก่อตัดสินใจจ้างจิระมาสวมบทเป็น ‘มิสเตอร์เค’ ตัวแทนเจรจาธุรกิจ เพื่อแลกกับเงื่อนไขที่ดูเรียบง่ายอย่างการที่ก่อต้องมาเป็นแบบในภาพวาดของจิระ
 แต่เมื่อร่างกายเริ่มเข้าใกล้ เส้นแบ่งระหว่างแรงบันดาลใจกับแรงปรารถนาก็เริ่มพร่าเลือน...
จากนายจ้างกลายเป็นสัมพันธ์ต้องห้ามที่ทั้งร้อนแรงและซับซ้อน ก่อจุดไฟให้งานศิลปะของจิระ ในขณะเดียวกันจิระก็จุดไฟในใจเขา และยิ่งไฟนั้นลุกแรงเท่าไรก่อก็ตระหนักได้ว่าคนที่พร้อมจะเผาไหม้ไปด้วยกันอาจไม่ใช่แค่พวกเขาสองคน ทว่ายังมีเพื่อนสนิทอย่าง ภีม (ดิว จิรวรรตน์) ที่กำลังก้าวเข้ามาเป็นคู่แข่งในเกมรักครั้งนี้ด้วยหัวใจที่พร้อมเดิมพันเช่นเดียวกัน
 “ท่ามกลางความแนบชิดของคนสองสามคน จิระยังคงสับสนในความสัมพันธ์ระหว่างเขากับก่อและตัวเขากับภีมแบบไหนคือความรักที่ต้องการจากใจจริงกันแน่”  ติดตามได้ใน Burnout Syndrome ภาวะรักคนหมดไฟ ทุกวันพุธ เวลา 20:30 น. ทางช่อง GMM25 และดูออนไลน์ เวลา 21:30 น. บนแอป iQIYI และเว็บ iQ.com ที่เดียวเท่านั้น เริ่ม 26 พฤศจิกายนนี้

snippet.title: 10DANCE | Official Trailer | Netflix
snippet.description:
Pride clashes and bodies entwine as two polar opposites are drawn together by love and breathtaking dance.

Inouesatoh's hit manga "10 DANCE" depicts the passion, anguish, jealousy and love shared between two men wholly devoted to dance. Now, this sweetly stimulating story of dance and love between two men is being adapted into a live-action Netflix Film! 

The story follows two men: Shinya Suzuki (Ryoma Takeuchi), Japan’s Latin dance champion, and Shinya Sugiki (Keita Machida), often called "Emperor," Japan’s ballroom dance champion and ranked second in the world. One day, Sugiki appears before Suzuki and proposes that the two of them become champions of the 10 Dance: an extremely demanding competition that requires both physical and mental fortitude, as participants must master 10 styles of dance — five Latin and five ballroom — and perform them all in a single day. Suzuki and Sugiki commence training at Sugiki Dance School accompanied by their respective dance partners, Aki Tajima (Shiori Doi) and Fusako Yagami (Anna Ishii). The two men clash as a result of their conflicting lifestyles and personalities, yet as they begin to understand each other’s style of dance, they find themselves drawn closer to one another.

The Netflix Film "10DANCE" starts streaming worldwide on Thursday, December 18, 2025, only on Netflix.

Starring: Ryoma Takeuchi, Keita Machida
Shiori Doi, Anna Ishii, Shinya Hamada, Oshiro Maeda
Nadiya Bychkova, Susie Trayling, Pasquale La Rocca
Based on the manga "10 DANCE" by Inouesatoh (serialized in Weekly Young Magazine by Kodansha)
Directed by Keishi Otomo
https://www.netflix.com/10DANCE

snippet.title: The Devil Wears Prada 2 | Teaser Trailer
snippet.description:
A sequel? For spring? Groundbreaking. Meryl Streep, Anne Hathaway, Emily Blunt, and Stanley Tucci return in The Devil Wears Prada 2, in theaters May 1, 2026. Watch the teaser trailer now. 

Almost twenty years after making their iconic turns as Miranda, Andy, Emily and Nigel—Meryl Streep, Anne Hathaway, Emily Blunt and Stanley Tucci return to the fashionable streets of New York City and the sleek offices of Runway Magazine in the eagerly awaited sequel to the 2006 phenomenon that defined a generation. 
 
The film reunites the original main cast with director David Frankel and writer Aline Brosh McKenna, and introduces an all-new runway of characters including Kenneth Branagh, Simone Ashley, Justin Theroux, Lucy Liu, Patrick Brammall, Caleb Hearon, Helen J. Shen, Pauline Chalamet, B.J. Novak and Conrad Ricamora. Tracie Thoms and Tibor Feldman also reprise their roles as “Lily” and “Irv” from the first film. 
 
“The Devil Wears Prada 2” is produced by Wendy Finerman, and executive produced by Michael Bederman, Karen Rosenfelt and McKenna. The film debuts exclusively in theaters May 1, 2026.
